<br>
Just as I was strapping my boots back on, being careful to avoid matting my freshly groomed foothair, a guildmate came up to me out of breath. I didn't see him at first, until he stepped out of his camouflage. It was then I noticed he was badly bruised and missing all of his gear. <br>
<br>
I asked, &quot;What happened to you? You look horrible!&quot;<br>
<br>
He replied, &quot; I was out hunting with some friends, and saw this merchant out in the middle of the fields. I decided to check out what he had for sale, but while I did, a storm rolled in off the water. The accompanying fog made it difficult to see. To keep from being ambushed, I ran with the Spirit of the Wolf. However, I got twisted around trying to get back to my friends. Visibility was bad, and I didn't see the drop-off. I crashed to the bottom of the chasm and a part of me died when I was smashed to a pulp on the rocks below.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What a horror!&quot; I responded. &quot;Have you tried to recover your gear?&quot;<br>
<br>
He sighed and sadly responded, &quot;I have made several failed attempts, each time leaving another part of me.&quot; He sighed deeply. &quot;Even more disturbing is that I have been doing this for so long now, I fear I'll even get my gear back.&quot; He sat down with his hands tucked under his chin. <br>
<br>
&quot;How did you try to recover your gear?&quot; I inquired. <br>
<br>
&quot;I levitated myself and floated down while camouflaged. I found my gear with some difficulty, but couldn't find a safe place to strap it back on. And as I was looking for a safe place, my camouflage faded. I don't even know where my corpse is at now!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, I hear that rogues are supposed to be good at getting into places they shouldn't be. Want me to take a shot at it?&quot;<br>
<br>
He pondered the offer. &quot;I don't want you to die down there. There's nasty critters down there...like a bizarre cross between a man and a scorpion. And I believe they are dreaded shadow knights as well...for as soon as I appeared, their foul touch sapped away my very life.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What are the alternatives?&quot;<br>
<br>
He sighed deeply. &quot;You're right...if my gear is even still there, this might be my last chance to get it back.&quot;<br>
<br>
I searched my backpack to see if I had a map of the area...even a crude map. I bit back a moan as I realized I had none.<br>
<br>
He escorted me to the edge of the chasm. Looking across it, and down into it, I realized that this was a huge place to be searching for his stuff. In addition, it seemed the floor was moving. He allowed me to run with the Spirit of the Wolf, and I carefully picked my way through the shadows looking for a safe way down. I figured that getting his gear wouldn't matter if I couldn't find my way out afterwards. <br>
<br>
After about 15 minutes of searching, I found a passable slope down. What I saw down there shocked me! There weren't one or two of those man/scorpions down here...there was a whole <br>
swarm of them! They were going in and out of ruined buildings, up and down ramps, patrolling the chasm floor. I panicked for a second, maybe three. <br>
<br>
I kept the feelings of terror in check however. My friend needed me. I carefully picked my way around the chasm floor. After about 20 minutes of searching, I spotted something on one of the ramps. It was a couple of pieces of his gear! While it wasn't all of his adventuring gear, it looked like a weapon and some foraged food he must have been using to aid him in getting his main gear back. I carefully dragged it back out of the chasm up the slope to where he was waiting. Even though it wasn't the bulk of his gear, our moods lifted tremendously. I had gone into the belly of the beast and had come back out again with something to show for it. <br>
<br>
I went back in to where I found his gear and resumed my search there. I figured the main body of stuff must be nearby. Instead I found a second of his recovery outfittings. I returned that to him as well. He informed me that there should only be the main goal of my crawl left: his main gear. After searching around there for about 30 minutes, sweat starting to pour from my forehead, I decided to sit down on a rock and ponder what to do. His gear, if not totally gone already, would probably not last much longer in this foul place.  I looked up at the sky to see how high he must have fallen from.<br>
<br>
What did I see when I looked up, but a gauntlet sticking out of a crevice! Upon closer examination, I recognized my friend's gear! However, try as I might, I couldn't drag it free! Dejected at my ultimate failure, I slinked back out of the chasm to inform my friend of my failure.<br>
<br>
<br>
(OOC) My ranger friend, and guildmate, had this happen to him. He died twice more trying to get his corpse. He told me he only had about 2-3 hours left before his corpses would start decaying. So I took the chance. We got two corpses but his main corpse was stuck in the geography. He petitioned, but given the urgency, he sent a tell to a guide. The guide immediately came and checked out the corpse, verifying it was stuck. He then summoned the corpse to a safe spot where my friend could loot it. During the whole time, only one guildmate made a brief appearance on server, and offered encouragement.<br>
<br>
That night at work, I printed out the map of all the zones I could so I'd be more prepared for the next time.<br>
